{"questionId":"2672753","questionHtml":"<div class=\"qb-parent-stem\"><p>Consider a geometric sequence, <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mi>n</mi></msub></math>, where <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>2</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>1</mn></msub></math> and&nbsp;<math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>4</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><msub><mi>u</mi><mn>6</mn></msub></math>.</p></div>\n<div class=\"qb-leaf-prompt\"><p>Given that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>99</mn></msub><mo>&lt;</mo><mn>0</mn></math>, find <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>5</mn></msub></math>.</p></div>","markschemeHtml":"<p>recognition that <math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><mi>r</mi></math> is negative&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>(M1)</strong></em></p>\n<p><math xmlns=\"http://www.w3.org/1998/Math/MathML\"><msub><mi>v</mi><mn>5</mn></msub><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mn>15</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mo>&nbsp;</mo><mfenced><mrow><mo>=</mo><mo>-</mo><mfrac><mn>45</mn><msqrt><mn>3</mn></msqrt></mfrac></mrow></mfenced></math>&nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp; &nbsp;&nbsp;<em><strong>A1</strong></em></p>\n<p>&nbsp;</p>\n<p><em><strong>[2 marks]</strong></em></p>","meta":{"questionId":"2672753","referenceCode":"23M.1.SL.TZ1.8e","subjectId":"50-dp-mathematics-analysis-and-approaches","title":"Given that v99<0, find v5.","paper":"1","level":"SL","questionNumber":"e","marksAvailable":"[Maximum mark: 2]","breadcrumbLabels":["Topic 1—Number and algebra","Topic 1—Number and algebra","SL 1.3—Geometric sequences and series"],"memberSectionIds":[],"sectionOrders":{}},"schemaVersion":3}
